# Python ML Serving Rules

## Async Inference (mandatory — D-03)
NEVER call `model.predict()` directly in an async endpoint. ALWAYS use `run_in_executor`:

```python
_executor = ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=4, thread_name_prefix="ml-infer")

@app.post("/predict")
async def predict(data: InputSchema):
    loop = asyncio.get_running_loop()
    return await loop.run_in_executor(_executor, partial(_sync_predict, data.model_dump()))
```

## SHAP (mandatory — D-04)
NEVER `TreeExplainer` with pipelines/ensembles. ALWAYS `KernelExplainer` in ORIGINAL feature space:

```python
def predict_proba_wrapper(X_array):
    X_df = pd.DataFrame(X_array, columns=original_feature_names)  # original space
    return pipeline.predict_proba(X_df)[:, 1]

explainer = shap.KernelExplainer(model=predict_proba_wrapper, data=X_background[:50])
```

## Other Rules
- Model loaded ONCE at startup (lifespan handler) — never per-request
- Endpoints: `/predict`, `/predict?explain=true`, `/health`, `/metrics`
- Mandatory Prometheus metrics: `{service}_predictions_total`, `{service}_request_duration_seconds`
- `uvicorn --workers 1` only (D-01)
- SHAP bg must have both classes (D-07)
